	Brosnan bother    
	 Los Angeles, April 17 (PTI): A shadow of doubt has been cast over filming of the sequel to actor Pierce Brosnans film The Thomas Crown Affair, after director Paul Verhoeven quit the project in a dispute over the script.      
	The former James Bond star is planning to reprise his role as a high-class art thief in a sequel to the 1999 thriller, which was a remake of a 1968 film starring Steve McQueen.      
	Brosnan confirmed the project in February this year, insisting movie bosses had a script and a structure that is good. However, the movie landed in a rough patch after Total Recall director Verhoeven walked out, reports Moviehole.net.    
	Wife video    
	London (PTI): Actor Russell Crowe has stepped into a directors shoes by reportedly directing his wife in a music video. The Gladiator star is married to Australian singer Danielle Spencer who has revived her music career in recent months with her first new album in eight years, Calling All Magicians. Crowe had earlier directed the music video clip for his Spencers single Tickle Me.     
	Ricky nude    
	 London (PTI): After finally coming out of the closet, Ricky Martin does not want to hold anything back and will be seen naked for the first time in his next video. The Latin superstar is completely nude except for a few well-placed digital tattoos, reported the Daily Mail. Martin sent out a link to the risque video Skin Talks, a promo for his upcoming Black amp; White tour, to his followers on Twitter.     
	Cole split    
	London (PTI): Singer Cheryl Cole is reportedly planning to divorce Ashley Cole despite the Chelsea and England footballers repeated attempts to win his estranged wife back. The X Factor judge has started working on a dignified divorce from Ashley following the cheating scandal that broke out in February.                                                                                                                                                       
